The paper deals with automated driving, which is a subfield of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed approach involves using deep reinforcement learning (DRL) and computer vision (cs.CV) to navigate in an urban environment, which falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses safety measures and penalties, which are related to control systems (cs.SY).
